-- Capital Trust Group Fund Invests $20 Million in Sakson Petroleum
-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 2012-08-28T07:34:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/capital-trust-group-fund-invests-20-million-in-sakson-petroleum.html
Capital Trust Group said its
EuroMena II fund invested $20 million to increase the capital of
Sakson Petroleum Services Holding S.A.L., an Egypt-based
provider of oil and natural-gas drilling services.  The investment will help fund expansion plans of Sakson
Petroleum, which runs projects in the  Middle East  and  Africa 
including Iraq, Kenya, Tanzania and Somalia, according to an e-
mailed statement, citing Romen Mathieu, managing director of
EuroMena II.  Capital Trust Group plans to start a EuroMena III fund,
which would be the companyâ€™s fourth private equity fund in the
Middle East and Africa region, with a value of $200 million to
$300 million, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
